---
import aboutImg from "@/assets/about-kesku.png";
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

const meta = {
	description: "I'm Kesku, a community-builder, tech enthusiast, and student. Learn more about me and my work.",
	title: "About Me, Kesku",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<div class="space-y-6">
		<h1 class="title">About me, Kesku</h1>
		<div class="justify-left flex">
			<Image
				alt="twitter profile picture of Kesku, art is of Usada Pekora from Hololive by @isukash"
				fetchpriority="high"
				loading="eager"
				src={aboutImg}
				style={{ width: "200px", height: "auto" }}
			/>
		</div>
		<sub class="text-center">
			Art by <a href="https://twitter.com/isukash" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">@isukash</a>
		</sub>

		<p>
			Hey, I’m Kesku — a UK-based student and hobbyist ML Engineer. I’ve spent the last few years helping build and moderate large-scale communities, most notably as a Senior Moderator at the <a href="https://discord.gg/openai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">OpenAI Discord</a>, which reached a peak of 3/5 million members! I also previously worked at 2 AI startups over the past 2 years in SWE/AI roles (~1 year of experience in total).
		</p>

		<p>
			I'm really passionate about AI, moderation, and digital spaces that feel both human and helpful. I'm also a full-time student (for now), and I try to keep things balanced between work, study, and occasionally touching grass. Or at least touching a controller.
		</p>

		<p>
			In my spare time, I game a lot. Lifelong Minecraft player (since 2011), big fan of <a href="https://yakuza.sega.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">Yakuza</a>, <a href="https://zzz.hoyoverse.com/en-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">Zenless Zone Zero</a>, <a href="https://www.cyberpunk.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">Cyberpunk 2077</a>, and GTA Online. I’ve also been known to rewrite moderation guides at 3AM.
		</p>

		<h2 class="title">"Kesku" is an acronym.</h2>
		<p>It stands for:</p>
		<ul class="list-inside list-disc">
			<li style="color: #10a7b2;"><strong>K</strong>eep</li>
			<li style="color: #10a7b2;"><strong>E</strong>verything</li>
			<li style="color: #10a7b2;"><strong>S</strong>imple</li>
			<li style="color: #10a7b2;"><strong>K</strong>eep</li>
			<li style="color: #10a7b2;"><strong>U</strong>nderstanding</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			It’s a mindset I try to carry into everything I do: make things understandable, approachable, and clear. Especially when working in fast-moving, high-stakes communities where clarity makes all the difference.
		</p>

		<p>
			You can find me on <a href="https://x.com/yoimnotkesku" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">Twitter</a>, <a href="https://github.com/kesku" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">GitHub</a>, and <a href="https://discordapp.com/users/539468067923820546" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">Discord</a> (<code>kesku</code>). You can also reach me at <a href="mailto:admin@kesku.me" style="color: #10a7b2; text-decoration: underline;">admin@kesku.me</a>.
		</p>

		<h2 class="title">This blog?</h2>
		<p>
			It’s mostly vibes. I ramble about tech, life, and whatever weird project I’ve picked up that week. I’m not trying to be a thought leader. I'm just a guy with a keyboard and way too many browser tabs.
		</p>

		<p>kes out</p>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
